Mexican Stocks: Cemex, Telmex Shares Declines; Azteca Advances

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-03-09T21:25:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/mexican-stocks-cemex-telmex-shares-declines-azteca-advances.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 0.7 percent to 36,450.19.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, fell 2.7 percent to 10.39 pesos. Cemex yesterday
announced plans to sell as much as $1.38 billion of notes
convertible to its U.S. shares.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB MM), the country’s largest
mining company, dropped 2.3 percent to 43.10 pesos. Copper fell
to the lowest in more than two months on concern that demand
will wane as higher energy costs slow the global economy.  Telefonos de Mexico SAB (TELMEXL MM), Mexico’s largest
fixed-line telephone company, dropped 1.7 percent to 10.57
pesos. The company plans to split into two companies to separate
its phone business in rural and low-income areas. Telmex may use
the split to create a new share listing.  TV Azteca SAB (TVAZTCPO MM), Mexico’s second-largest
broadcast television network, gained 3.1 percent to 8.74 pesos.
The company had its 12-month price-target raised by Credit
Suisse AG analyst Andrew Campbell.  To contact the reporter on this story:
